gotermx Help

  M-x      Command palette       M-d      Toggle dired (M-x set-pwd)
  M-t      Toggle terminal       M-e      Toggle code editor
  M-w      Copy selection         M-W      Cut selection
  M-y      Paste clipboard
  (no welcome screen — clean startup)

  ── C-x Prefix ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
  C-f      Find file (create)     C-d      Open dir in dired
  C-t      New terminal split     C-w      Close pane
  C-e      Exec shell cmd         C-c      Copy selection
  C-x      Cut selection          C-v      Paste clipboard
  1        Focus only pane        0        Kill pane
  o        Focus other pane       r        Resize splits
  p        Dired cd here          n        New file
  N        New directory          d        Delete (confirm)
  R        Rename selected        f        Filter dired files
  ←/→      Adjust split           C-g      Stop all plugins
  C-z      Plugin prompt (C-x C-z)

  ── Editor ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   C-s      Save file             C-o      New buffer
  C-f      Find (highlights all) C-r      Find & Replace
  C-g      Goto line             ↑/↓      Nav search matches
  Enter    Replace mode: first Enter confirms find + jumps to 1st match,
           type replacement, Enter replaces and advances to next
  C-h      Replace all           Esc      Exit replace / clear selection
  C-n/C-p  Next/prev line        C-a      Select all
  C-e      Line end              C-k      Kill line
  C-w      Close buffer          C-d      Delete forward
  C-v      Page down             Tab      Indent (with sel)
  S-Tab    Previous buffer       S-arrows Extend selection
  C-Space  Set selection mark    M-w      Copy to clipboard
  M-W      Cut selection         M-y      Paste clipboard
  C-z      Undo                  C-y      Redo
  M-/      Fuzzy autocomplete    ↑↓  Navigate completions
  M-←      Strip leading+trailing ws  M-↑/↓   Move line up/down
  M-k      Delete line
  C-←/→    Word left/right       C-↑/↓    5 lines up/down
  S-C-←/→  Select word           S-C-↑/↓  Select 5 lines
  Selection auto-clears on non-Shift movement (arrows, Home/End, PgUp/Dn)

  ── Editor Micro Splits ─────────────────────────────────────────
  M-z v    Vertical split        M-z h    Horizontal split
  M-z r    Resize mode           ←/→/↑/↓ Adjust boundary
  M-z c    Close split           M-z o    Switch split
  M-z t    Toggle orientation    (max 4 splits)

  ── Terminal ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Built-in PTY-based shell with full ANSI support.
  Hidden by default — C-x t to create; background matches theme.
  Persistent shell (auto-restarts), up to 3 terminal splits.
  ↑/↓      Shell history          PgUp/PgDn  Scroll back
  C-l      Clear screen            C-c      Interrupt
  C-d      EOF / exit

  ── Terminal Splits ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  M-z v    Vertical split        M-z h    Horizontal split
  M-z c    Close split           M-z o    Switch split
  M-s      Resize mode           ←/→/↑/↓ Adjust boundary
  (max 3 splits, auto-restart on exit)

  ── File Browser (Dired) ────────────────────────────────────────
  ls-la style listing in editor buffer. M-d to toggle, C-x C-d to
  open a specific dir (prompt with auto-create). Sets global PWD.
  j/k      Move down/up          g/G      Top/bottom
  Enter    Open file/dir         -/Bksp   Parent directory
  C-x f    Filter by name        C-x n    New file
  C-x N    New directory         C-x d    Delete (confirm)
  C-x R    Rename selected       C-x p    Cd here

  ── Command Split (C-x C-e) ──
  Run shell command — output streams live (50ms flush ticker,
  updates continuously even without newlines).
  Tab completes paths, input has shell syntax highlighting
  (commands, flags, strings, vars, operators, comments).
  C-c      Abort running command   C-w/Esc Close output buffer
  ↑/↓      Scroll output         ←/→/H/E Word-move, line start/end

  ── C-z Plugins ──────────────────────────────────────────────
  C-x C-z  Plugin prompt (type,↑↓,Tab,Enter)  type n   New plugin buffer
  C-z      Undo last edit                       C-y      Redo last edit
  C-x C-g  Stop running plugin          ↑↓/Tab  Navigate/complete

  ── Plugins ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  M-x list-plugins  Plugin Manager   C-x C-g  Stop all plugins
  C-x 1  Run selected plugin   C-x 2  Stop selected
  C-x 3  Toggle favorite        ★  Favorites listed first

  ── Footer Prompts ────────────────────────────────────────────────
  All prompts and popups appear in the footer bar (Emacs/Vim style).
  Type in the footer input line; drop-up list shown above.
  ↑↓ navigate list  Tab/Enter complete  Esc cancel
  ← →/C-← C-→ Move char/word    Home/End  Line start/end
  M-p/M-n  Cycle prompt input history      Recent cmds at top of M-x
  C-x C-e prompt: shell syntax highlighted + path completion (Tab)

  ── Per-Split Footer ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  Each editor microsplit has its own footer bar:
  "Line: XXXX Col: XXXX    (LangName: .ext)"
  Language name detected from syntax highlighting by extension.
  Msg bar flashes OkText for 3s, then reverts to muted gray.
  M-x toggle-scroll-mode  Switch between 1-line and 12-line scroll
  M-x set-tab-width       Set Tab width (spaces)

  ── Multi-Cursor (Emacs-style) ─────────────────────────────────
  C-x C-SPC  Mark next occurrence         C-x C-n    Mark all occurrences
  C-x RET    Toggle multi-edit mode       C-x Esc    Clear all cursors
  (Arrow keys, Home/End move all cursors in parallel. Edit any, edits all.)

  ── AI Plugin (ai.lua) ──────────────────────────────────────────
  M-x run-plugin  Select "ai" to start Ollama chat
  Select a model, then type messages in the footer prompt.
  AI can execute bash commands via RUN_BASH: <cmd> pattern.
  Streaming output auto-wraps within editor width.
  Requires: Ollama running at http://localhost:11434

  ── Plugin API (Lua) ────────────────────────────────────────────
  editor.append_text  Append to buffer    editor.width  Get editor width
  streamToken(token)  Append with word wrap   http.get/post  HTTP reqs
  json.encode/decode  JSON utils         All plugins in ~/.config/goterm/plugins/

  ── Reloading Config ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  M-x reload-syntax       Reload .syntax files from disk
  M-x reload-theme        Reload .theme files from disk
  M-x reload-plugins      Reload plugins from disk
  M-x find-plugins        Scan dirs and load new plugins

